<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06160084 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06160084 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  SAN-JOSE; MURDER; MULTIPLE; ARREST  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  San Jose police announced Friday that they had arrested two men on suspicionof murdering a 33-year-old San Jose man after a car chase in early March. Thetwo San Jose men, Gerardo Mechaca, a 26-year-old roofer, and Hector ArturoOropeza, 26, were being held without bail at Santa Clara County Jail.;    Sgt.Glenn McCourtie said the two are suspected of stabbing Richard Figueroa todeath near Kenbrook Circle and Southside Drive -- a little south of the countyfairgrounds -- early March 2.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  PAIR ARRESTED IN MARCH SLAYING OF SAN JOSEMAN  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     Investigators said the two men had chased Figueroa in a car as he was onhis way to a friend's home.;    The motive for the attack remained murkyFriday, and officers did not explain what led to the arrests.;    &quot;At first,it seemed like a totally unprovoked attack,&quot; said Sgt. Greg Trapp, a policespokesman. &quot;They're looking now at the possibility of an altercation earlierin the evening.&quot;  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News Staff Report  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910608  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Saturday  </DAY><MONTH>  June  </MONTH><PG.COL>  8B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  154  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Saturday June 8, 199100160084,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>